{
 "name": "RPlog_En_Route_to_Destiny",
 "title": "En Route to Destiny",
 "summary": "Storming back aboard his heavily modified ship Uwannabuyim at Pride-1, the mechanic-Jedi Orson grimly announces to Jessalyn that they are leaving at once: his slicer, who pinpointed the coordinates matching a shared vision, has gone missing, and Simon, who saw the same vision, may be involved. The malfunctioning protocol droid TooSock (2SK-MI), newly adapting crude spacer slang and prone to losing his head, provides comic relief while Jessalyn tinkers to fix his failing balance. Orson explains they are bound for an uncharted system reconstructed from the constellation in his vision, with no idea what awaits them, and Jessalyn reassures him through the Force that pursuing it is the right thing despite the uncertainty. As Orson powers up the ship and slips into the cockpit, TooSock probes Jessalyn on what drives her, drawing out both her conviction that all of them have Seen the vision and a quiet admission that she will go anywhere so long as Orson is there. The droid muses about pattern-recognition and love before abruptly powering down mid-sentence, leaving Jessalyn at her repairs as the Uwannabuyim rumbles toward its mysterious destiny.",
